==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: modal auxiliary
<hw>mo"dal aux*il"iar*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <fld>(Gram.)</fld>,
<pos>n.</pos> <def>Any one of the auxiliary verbs of English, such as
<examp>can</examp>, <examp>may</examp>, <examp>will</examp>,
<examp>shall</examp>, <examp>must</examp>, <examp>might</examp>,
<examp>could</examp>, <examp>would</examp>, or <examp>should</examp>,
which are used together with the infinitive form of another verb to
express distinctions of mood{2}, such as uncertainty, possibility,
command, emphasis, and obligation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Modalist</ent>⟦br⟧
